<br>
if we do not stop saddam, we will all die. -- die from what?<br>
he has the weapons. -- does he?<br>
he will use them.  -- use what now?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Ok, about 15 years ago, Saddam invaded his neighbor.  We kicked his ass.  Since then we (as in the united states and allies) have been flying over 2/3 of his country partolling the &quot;no-fly-zones&quot; that we set up because we won the war.  Since then, Saddam has shot at our planes over Iraqi soil, he's made threats against the united states, and he shrugs his shoulders and doesnt care about the US when 9/11 happens.<br>
<br>
We have threatened to invade Iraq because:<br>
A) He has weapons of mass distruction<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>response</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> - Still lookin for proof on that one chief.  Some say he's denying it, but could it actually be possible that he doesnt have them?  Ohh wait i have a reality check coming...  We've monitored just about everything we have been able to going in and out of Iraq.  We've ceased things that have a &quot;dual-use&quot; -- things like microwave ovens and other deadly materials (note:sarcasm.)  Even if he wanted to have these weapons, it would have been very difficult to do over the 1/3 of the country saddam has more or less full reign over.  Now this is not to say that if he had the resources would he have made WOMD (please let me sum it up, it's a stupid propaganda phrase anyway).<br>
<br>
B) He supports Al-Quadea<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>response</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> - Ohh wait, we're still lookin for proof on that too.  No doubt in my mind that Saddam loves watching the US suffer.  Is this right?  No, no one should be happy in the suffer of another.  Does it warrant war?  Absolutely not.<br>
<br>
C) Oil<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>response</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> - Now this is the one that makes little sense, but I highly doubt the US would go to war over just oil.  I'm not the biggest Pres. Bush fan out there, but i'll give him the benefit of the doubt over this.  This is a conspiracy theory.  Could it be true?  Yea it could be, but in 30 years when the documents become public we'll know about it and declare Bush the worst President ever, blah blah blah...  I don't think he wants that.<br>
<br>
------<br>
<br>
I again form my opinion that this is a buildup in order to scare Saddam with complying with UN resolutions.  Bush is playing the heavy hand here.  If he backs down then other countries will feel that the US has become soft and *that* is what will bite us in the ass more than anything.  Is Saddam a bad person?  Yea, but so are 1/2 of the other dictators in the world.  I'd bet that there are just as many worse than him than are better. (that is all speculation, just making the point that there are others in the world worse than him) <br>
<br>
Vatikus, trying to scare us into hating someone might work on some.  But really, in all likelyhood, nothing of what you described could happen in the near future.  If saddam ever had nuclear weapons (which he doesn't -- Pres. Bush's advisors stipulate to that even) then he'd have to get it to the united states somehow first.  And that will not happen for quite some time.  I'm more worried about something like that happening from Al-Qaeda or some other rogue group than Iraq. <p>**********Quellious*********<br>
